title: Texas teen dies after being put in chokehold while wrestling
text:
Texas teen dies after being put in chokehold while wrestling By   
SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) - Police in Central Texas say a 17-year-old has died after being placed in a chokehold while wrestling with another teen at a sleepover. 
San Marcos police say Elijah Hernandez died early Sunday morning. Police say he and six other friends were at a home for a sleepover when he and another 17-year-old started wrestling, with the teen putting Hernandez in a chokehold neck restraint and telling him to indicate when he was giving up. When the teen passed out, the other teen released his hold. 
Police say the father at the house started CPR and 911 was called. 
Hernandez was pronounced dead at the hospital. His cause of death is pending an autopsy. 
Police spokeswoman Kristi Wyatt says police have determined the death was accidental and don’t plan charges.
